Summit, NJ Map:

View Larger Map
Directions from Newark Liberty International Airport (EWR) by train:

Take the AirTrain from the airport terminal to the Newark Liberty International Train Station (also referred to as rail link system). From there, take either the Northeast Corridor or North Jersey Coast Line trains to Secaucus Junction. At Secaucus, catch a train on the Morristown Line, Dover or Gladstone Branch to Summit (usually on the “Dover” train). Once you arrive in Summit, you are only a few blocks from the office.
Exit the train station on the Union Place (North) side of the tracks, and continue across the street traveling on Beechwood Rd. one block. Take a left on Springfield Avenue, and go about two blocks to 450 Springfield Ave., which will be on the left-hand side. SeaBridge is located on the third floor of 450 Springfield Ave. in Suite 301.
You can always ask a New Jersey Transit employee at a ticket window what trains are the best option to get you to Summit as schedules are not the same on each day. You may also check the train schedule online at njtransit.com. Approximate travel time is 1 to 2 hours depending on how frequently trains are departing upon your arrival in Newark.

Directions from New York Penn Station by train:

Take the New Jersey Transit’s Morris & Essex Line to Summit (usually on the “Dover” train). Once you arrive in Summit, you are only a few blocks from the office.
Exit the train station on the Union Place (North) side of the tracks, and continue across the street traveling on Beechwood Rd. one block. Take a left on Springfield Avenue, and go about two blocks to 450 Springfield Ave., which will be on the left-hand side. SeaBridge is located on the third floor of 450 Springfield Ave. in Suite 301.
You can always ask a New Jersey Transit employee at a ticket window what trains are the best option to get you to Summit as schedules are not the same on each day. You may also check the train schedule online at njtransit.com. The local train takes roughly 55 minutes, while the express can take 30 minutes.

Directions from Newark Liberty International Airport (EWR) by car:

From the airport terminal, follow the signs to I-78 West and travel roughly 8 miles. I-78 splits, so bear to the right on RT-24 West towards Springfield/Morristown. Take the first exit, #9A, to Summit and bear right on Broad Street and travel roughly 0.5 miles. Turn right on to Springfield Avenue and travel just over a mile into downtown Summit. Our office is located across the street form where Woodland Ave enters Springfield from the right. This is a “T-shaped” intersection. 450 is a red brick building with stores on the first floor.
If you get to Winberries, where Kent Place Blvd enters Springfield, you have gone a block too far. Turn into the alley on the left just past 450 and park on the ground level. If this lot is full there is a larger lot one block off Springfield, on Woodland.
Approximate travel time is 30 minutes in light traffic








 


