About | SeaBridge Investment Advisors, LLC















Toggle navigation














    About  
 SeaBridge Investment Advisors, LLC, an SEC-Registered Investment Advisor, is based in Summit, NJ, with a research office in Atlanta, GA. SeaBridge analyzes a global universe of securities and creates investment portfolios in different styles to meet different investor needs. We are long-only value investors. We are not a hedge fund. We do not use exotic securities in client portfolios.
For individuals, SeaBridge builds customized portfolios of listed global equities to meet their specific risk profile, income needs and investment horizon. Please feel free to look over our strategies section. SeaBridge then actively manages these portfolios, reflecting its analysis of the global economic and market environments, the attractiveness of the securities, and the client’s changing needs. Through this customization, SeaBridge offers a service which is differentiated from:

Mutual funds, where a client’s needs must fit the fund; and
Those investment advisors who focus primarily on asset allocation and funds and do not attempt to capture the upside in individual stock selection.

Institutional clients generally select one of our pure investment style portfolios, which can be found in the strategies section of our website.
At SeaBridge, clients have their own individual portfolios and receive individual care and attention to their needs. Seasoned SeaBridge portfolio managers are available for consultation at any time.
SeaBridge was founded in 1996 by Garnett L. Keith, who served as the Chief Investment Officer of The Prudential Insurance Company of America from 1984 to 1996. With its U.S.-based professionals and, through its sub-advisory arrangements and other relationships with investment organizations in Hong Kong and Paris, SeaBridge has the resources to offer a global investment capability.
For a more thorough exposition of the SeaBridge approach to global equities, we invite you to explore our web site.














About — Seabridge Advisors
















































































About
Knowledge, Expertise, Experience




What We DoSeabridge Advisors LLC provides corporate development services to the knowledge economy. Client specialization includes corporate Learning & Development software/services, HR software/services, GRC solution providers and Knowledge Management. We advise and execute on buy-and sell-side M&A transactions, growth capital raising, channel development and strategic alliances. Special focus is on cross-border opportunities with international groups seeking to establish or grow their US footprint through acquisitions or partnerships. Seabridge has built relationships with a broad array of advisors across the DACH and BeneLux regions.Registered Representative of and Securities Products offered through BA Securities, LLC Member FINRA (www.FINRA.org) SIPC (www.SIPC.org). Seabridge Advisors LLC and BA Securities, LLC are separate and independent entities. Any testimonial or endorsement may not be representative of the experience of other customers and is no guarantee of future performance or success. Get in touchContact Seabridge to discuss your Corporate Development goals.Book an appointment ▸  






Registered Representative of and Securities Products offered through BA Securities, LLC Member FINRA SIPC.



David VickreyManaging principalDavid Vickrey has more than 25 years of corporate finance experience.  David formed Seabridge Advisors in 2016 to provide strategic advisory services to the Knowledge Economy.  Specialization includes Talent Management/HCM software and services, Enterprise Content Management and Collaboration technology, with a focus on facilitating cross-border transactions.  Prior to founding Seabridge, David was a partner at Gotham Growth, a boutique advisory firm providing outsourced Corporate Development services to the Talent Management/HCM sector.  From 2000 to 2008 David was Vice President of Corporate Development at SkillSoft Plc where he executed on both buy-side and sell-side M&A transactions and managed the group’s Strategic Alliances with Cisco Systems, Oracle and Microsoft.  Prior to SkillSoft, David worked in corporate finance in  Frankfurt and New York with Deutsche Bank Securities, Barclays Capital and Commerzbank AG. EducationDavid studied at Boston University, the Universities of Freiburg and Cologne (Germany) and earned a PhD from Harvard University (Graduate School of Arts & Sciences)LicensesSeries 79, 62 , and 63 securities licenses. "Wissen, Expertise, Erfahrung"











